The paper addresses the problem of jointly learning vision and language, which is a common theme in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The proposed architectures use CNN-LSTM networks, which are commonly used in deep learning (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves object retrieval, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR).
